OL,3,CLaw could change to protect sexual
OL,4,Cassault victims after death of teenager
OL,6,FMoves to improve police investigations
OL,7,Finto cases of rape and sexual assault
OL,8,Fcould become law following a campaign
OL,9,Fby the family of a teenage sexual
OL,10,Fassault victim who died.
OL,12,FGaia Pope, from Dorset, had made an
OL,13,Fallegation of rape but no case was
OL,14,Ftaken forward.
OL,16,FShe later ran away in November 2017
OL,17,Fand was reported missing. Her body was
OL,18,Ffound near Swanage. She died, aged 19,
OL,19,Fof hypothermia.
